transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, this is Charles.

Speaker 2: Yes, I'm calling to cancel my autopag.

Speaker 1: Okay, I've got Mario Derogatus.

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Thomas River, Arizona.

Speaker 1: No, New Jersey.

Speaker 2: Arizona or New Jersey? What the heck?

Speaker 1: Why does that say Arizona?

Speaker 2: All right, just fix that.

Speaker 1: Okay, it does look like you are a VIP member here, Mario.

Speaker 2: Are you just overstocked at this point, just don't need anything for a while?

Speaker 1: Need a pump and brakes?

Speaker 2: Well, I believe my first shipment was $119.

Speaker 1: Does it show that on there?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: It was $93.35 for the first order.

Speaker 2: It looks like it was the 50 milligram of the Viagra AGV,

Speaker 1: and then we have an online buy one get one half off,

Speaker 2: so $29.40 for an additional 10 pills, so you had 20 pills come to you the first time.

Speaker 1: Right, and then I just had 10 pills come to me now.

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: And what was the charge for that?

Speaker 2: $63.95 for the 10 pills.

Speaker 1: So yeah, if you'd like, I can just pause everything for the time being,

Speaker 2: let you get caught up with what you have,

Speaker 1: and then call us back and let us know what the best refill date should be.

Speaker 2: Okay, so they won't ship anything to me until I call back?

Speaker 1: Right, so what we do, typically what our VIP members will do,

Speaker 2: is we'll pause everything for six months at a time.

Speaker 1: That way it doesn't come every single month.

Speaker 2: You'd only get charged for the one for the year in August.

Speaker 1: That'd be it.

Speaker 2: Nothing else would come after that.

Speaker 1: You can call in and request them as needed whenever you need them.

Speaker 2: Okay, and then any time in between now I can still call back and cancel, correct?

Speaker 1: Exactly, exactly.

Speaker 2: All right, that's what we'll do, okay?

Speaker 1: Let's keep it until August.

Speaker 2: Okay, sounds good.

Speaker 1: All right, then.

Speaker 2: Just place that right now.

Speaker 1: I hope you have a great rest of your day, all right?

Speaker 2: All right, you too.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Have a good one.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
